AN unknown number of thugs bombed a cash safe at the Thulamahashe Plaza KFC in Bushbuckridge, Mpumalanga, yesterday. They made off with an undisclosed amount of cash. According to a security guard on patrol, they spotted an unknown number of thugs with guns smashing the shop’s glass door to gain entry. He then heard an explosion and alerted the police, who responded swiftly. Police spokesman Brigadier Leonard Hlathi confirmed the security guard was on duty when he saw an unknown number of suspects break the main door at KFC. “After a few minutes, he heard a huge explosion inside the shop. “He alerted the KFC manager and called police. “Upon arrival, police found the suspects long gone. “Preliminary investigations revealed the suspects bombed the cash safe and took an undisclosed amount of cash, laptop and a tablet,” said Hlathi. “They fled the scene in unknown vehicles. No arrests have been made at this stage.” He said a burglary case was opened. Anyone with information which could lead to the arrest of the suspects can contact Captain Malamba Khoza on 072 624 5133.